  "prompt": "What is the food you can eat every day for breakfast, lunch and dinner?",
  "response": "When considering a food that can be eaten every day for breakfast, lunch, and dinner, you would generally want something that is versatile, nutritionally balanced, and can be adapted to various recipes and preparations. One great option is eggs. \n\n**Eggs** are highly versatile and can be used in an array of dishes:\n- **Breakfast**: Scrambled eggs, omelets, or eggs benedict.\n- **Lunch**: Egg salad, quiche, or egg sandwiches.\n- **Dinner**: Stir-fried rice with eggs, frittatas, or shakshuka.\n\nEggs are rich in protein, vitamins, and minerals, making them a nutritional powerhouse. They can be combined with different vegetables, grains, and proteins to maintain variety and balance in your diet. However, while eggs can be a staple, it's important to have a variety of foods in your diet to ensure you get all necessary nutrients and avoid monotony.",
